<title>UK: First Direct to create over 5,000 jobs over 7 years - paper.</title>
<headline>First Direct to create over 5,000 jobs over 7 years - paper.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-04-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>First Direct, the telephone bank of Midland Bank, is to build a new call centre in Scotland that is expected to create 5,000 jobs over the next seven years, the Financial Times said on Wednesday.</p>
<p>The paper said First Direct, which has built up 650,000 customers since its launch in 1989, needed to expand to cope with the 12,000 customers it gained every month.</p>
<p>Construction of the new centre, at Hamilton near Glasgow, would begin next month, the Financial Times said.</p>
<p>-- Dan Lalor, London Newsroom +44 171 542 8863</p>
